Message-ID: <1898187B-9380-4214-9BD5-3133136FD1AB@mylesbraithwaite.com>

If anyone has some free time the following should get tackled soonish:

1) We need to put something on the website saying that your first message will be put in a moderation queue before you are allowed to post to the list, this is to prevent spammers. If someone could draft this up it would be really helpful. The page's source is located here: <https://github.com/gtalug/website/blob/master/pages/mailing-list.markdown>.

2) A couple of people have complained about the lack of a SSL certificate on the GTALUG.org web site (we do ask for a password with mailman sign ups). Could someone research how we could do this for free. Will this need to be renewed annually? Can a self-signed cert be okay? etc. 
