Message-ID: <CAJt6_8tPrspZ0pDuxyXHSuyhi1oVoryTDPAMx4Mi6S5SwpvFRA@mail.gmail.com>

Cloudflare has a free https option that I believe would support our needs.
It depends on SNI, but that's supported by all modern browsers / tools.
Plus on top of that, you get a free CDN and SPDY (a/k/a HTTP/2's
predecessor) support.

https://blog.cloudflare.com/introducing-universal-ssl/

-Greg

